searchData={"items":[{"type":"task","title":"mix spex","doc":"Mix task that checks saved implementation models for bisimilarity.\n\nThis is the offline verification entry point for `.spex` model files.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Spex.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Mix.Tasks.Spex.run/1","doc":"Runs Spex bisimilarity checks for all loaded implementation models.\n\nAccepts either no arguments (uses configured `:impl_models_dir`) or one path\nargument to a directory or file containing `.spex` models.","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Spex.html#run/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex","doc":"Entry point for Spex runtime APIs and high-level integration.\n\nSpex tracks observed runtime behaviour as implementation models and compares\nthose models to declarative specifications (LTSs). It is designed for:\n\n- online runtime observation (`init_instance*`, `transition*`),\n- detection/reporting of behavioural deviations,\n- export and offline checking of derived implementation models.","ref":"Spex.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Quick Start - Spex","doc":"1. Define one or more specifications with `Spex.Specification`.\n2. Start Spex (or an instance manager) under a supervisor.\n3. Initialize instances with `init_instance/4`.\n4. Feed observed transitions with `transition/3`.\n\nMinimal usage example:\n\n    :ok = Spex.init_instance(MySpec, :order_123)\n    :ok = Spex.transition(:order_123, :pay, :paid)\n    :ok = Spex.transition(:order_123, :ship, :shipped)","ref":"Spex.html#module-quick-start"},{"type":"module","title":"How To Start Spex - Spex","doc":"There are two primary integration styles.","ref":"Spex.html#module-how-to-start-spex"},{"type":"module","title":"1) Spex As Its Own OTP Application - Spex","doc":"This is the usual setup when the dependency is started normally\n(`runtime: true`, default). Your app depends on Spex and Spex boots its own\nsupervision tree.","ref":"Spex.html#module-1-spex-as-its-own-otp-application"},{"type":"module","title":"2) Explicit Supervision (runtime: false) - Spex","doc":"If Spex is configured with `runtime: false`, add either `Spex` or a concrete\ninstance manager directly to your supervision tree:\n\n    children = [\n      Spex\n    ]\n\nor:\n\n    children = [\n      {Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager,\n       impl_models_dir: \"./spex_impl_models\",\n       dets_dir: \"./spex_dets\"}\n    ]\n\nor:\n\n    children = [\n      {Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager,\n       distribution_factor: 8,\n       impl_models_dir: \"./spex_impl_models\",\n       dets_dir: \"./spex_dets\"}\n    ]","ref":"Spex.html#module-2-explicit-supervision-runtime-false"},{"type":"module","title":"Online Production Usage - Spex","doc":"In production, call `init_instance/4` when a domain entity begins its tracked\nlifecycle, then call `transition/3` for each observed state change.\n\nBehavioural checks and error handling are driven by the underlying\nspecification (`error_handler/2`, timeout settings, pruning rules).","ref":"Spex.html#module-online-production-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"ImplModel Derivation During Tests - Spex","doc":"Spex can derive implementation models from test execution and persist them as\n`.spex` files. The main purpose of this derivation flow is to run offline\nbisimilarity checks with the `mix spex` task.\n\nTypical flow:\n\n- call `Spex.Testing.prepare_for_test_suite/1` in test setup,\n- run tests while using normal Spex APIs,\n- after suite completion, derived models are exported,\n- run `mix spex` (or `mix spex  `) to validate derived models.\n\nExample:\n\n    # test/test_helper.exs\n    Spex.Testing.prepare_for_test_suite(impl_models_dir: \"./test_meta/impl_models/live\")\n\n    # CI or local verification\n    # Uses configured :impl_models_dir when no path is given\n    mix spex","ref":"Spex.html#module-implmodel-derivation-during-tests"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration Entry Point - Spex","doc":"This module delegates to a compile-time default instance manager selected via\n`config :spex, :instance_manager`.\n\nAccepted forms are:\n\n- `MyManagerModule`\n- `{MyManagerModule, manager_opts}`","ref":"Spex.html#module-configuration-entry-point"},{"type":"module","title":"Documentation Map - Spex","doc":"- `Spex.Specification`: define specifications and options.\n- `Spex.InstanceManager`: behaviour contract for manager implementations.\n- `Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager`: single-node manager setup.\n- `Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager`: sharded manager setup.\n- `Spex.Testing`: test helpers and suite-level model export.\n- `Spex.ImplModel` / `Spex.ImplModelStore`: model representation and storage.\n- `Spex.BisimilarityChecker`: bisimilarity validation internals.\n- `Mix.Tasks.Spex`: offline bisimilarity checks over saved `.spex` files.","ref":"Spex.html#module-documentation-map"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.action/0","doc":"Action label on transitions.\n\nConventional reserved actions used internally by Spex are:\n\n- `:__internal__` for unobservable/internal steps,\n- `:__initialisation__` for synthetic instance initialization transitions.","ref":"Spex.html#t:action/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.state/0","doc":"State label used in specifications and runtime observations.","ref":"Spex.html#t:state/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.transition/0","doc":"A labelled transition tuple `{from_state, action, to_state}`.","ref":"Spex.html#t:transition/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.child_spec/1","doc":"","ref":"Spex.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.export_impl_models/0","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.export_impl_models/0 .","ref":"Spex.html#export_impl_models/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.init_instance/4","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.init_instance/4 .","ref":"Spex.html#init_instance/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.init_instance!/4","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.init_instance!/4 .","ref":"Spex.html#init_instance!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.init_instance_async/4","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.init_instance_async/4 .","ref":"Spex.html#init_instance_async/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.transition/3","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.transition/3 .","ref":"Spex.html#transition/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.transition!/3","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.transition!/3 .","ref":"Spex.html#transition!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.transition_async/3","doc":"See  Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.transition_async/3 .","ref":"Spex.html#transition_async/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.Application","doc":"Application entrypoint for starting the Spex supervision tree.","ref":"Spex.Application.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker","doc":"Compares implementation models against specifications via branching bisimilarity.","ref":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.bisimilar_to_specification?/1","doc":"Compares an ImplModel against a Specification using bisimilarity checking.\n\nReturns `true` if the implementation model is bisimilar to the specification,\n`false` otherwise.","ref":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.html#bisimilar_to_specification?/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - Spex.BisimilarityChecker.bisimilar_to_specification?/1","doc":"- `impl_model`: A `%Spex.ImplModel{}` struct containing observed transitions\n- `specification`: A module implementing the `Spex.Specification` behaviour","ref":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.html#bisimilar_to_specification?/1-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - Spex.BisimilarityChecker.bisimilar_to_specification?/1","doc":"iex> impl_model = %Spex.ImplModel{...}\n    iex> Spex.BisimilarityChecker.bisimilar_to_specification?(impl_model, MySpecification)\n    true","ref":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.html#bisimilar_to_specification?/1-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.MercWrapper","doc":"Rust NIF wrapper used to execute bisimilarity checks.","ref":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.MercWrapper.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.MercWrapper.compare_bisimilarity/2","doc":"Compares implementation and specification LTS data for branching bisimilarity.","ref":"Spex.BisimilarityChecker.MercWrapper.html#compare_bisimilarity/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.Errors","doc":"Error types used across Spex runtime and persistence boundaries.","ref":"Spex.Errors.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.Errors.FileError","doc":"Alias type wrapper for file-system errors represented by `File.Error`.","ref":"Spex.Errors.FileError.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.FileError.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.FileError.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.Errors.Template","doc":"Macro for defining Spex exception modules with typed reasons and context.","ref":"Spex.Errors.Template.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.ImplModel","doc":"Represents the observed implementation model built from runtime transitions.","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.ImplModel.observation_status/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#t:observation_status/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.ImplModel.serialisation/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#t:serialisation/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.ImplModel.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.ImplModel.deserialise/1","doc":"Deserialises `.spex` content into an implementation model.","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#deserialise/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.ImplModel.initialise/1","doc":"Creates an empty implementation model for a specification in learning mode.","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#initialise/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.ImplModel.observe_transition/2","doc":"Observes a transition and returns its status and resulting model.\n\nIn learning mode, the transition is added. Outside learning mode, the model\nis checked for bisimilarity impact without mutating stored transitions.","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#observe_transition/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.ImplModel.serialise/1","doc":"Serialises an implementation model into `.spex` text format.","ref":"Spex.ImplModel.html#serialise/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.ImplModelStore","doc":"Loads and persists implementation models in `.spex` file format.","ref":"Spex.ImplModelStore.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.ImplModelStore.load/1","doc":"Loads all `.spex` models from a directory or a single file path.","ref":"Spex.ImplModelStore.html#load/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.ImplModelStore.save/2","doc":"Saves implementation models to the target directory.\n\nReturns all write errors if one or more files fail to persist.","ref":"Spex.ImplModelStore.html#save/2"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Spex.InstanceManager","doc":"Behaviour contract plus shared helpers for Spex instance managers.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.instance_manager_opt/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#t:instance_manager_opt/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.all_impl_models/0","doc":"Returns all currently known implementation models.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:all_impl_models/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.all_instances/0","doc":"Returns all instances managed by this instance manager.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:all_instances/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.all_instances/1","doc":"Returns all instances for a given specification module.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:all_instances/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a child spec for supervising the instance manager.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:child_spec/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.delete_instance/1","doc":"Deletes one instance by identifier.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:delete_instance/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.delete_instances/1","doc":"Deletes all instances matching the provided filter function.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:delete_instances/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.export_impl_models/0","doc":"Serialises and exports implementation models as `{filename, content}` tuples.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:export_impl_models/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.get_instance/1","doc":"Fetches one instance by identifier.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:get_instance/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance/4","doc":"Initializes a new instance and records initialisation as the first transition.\n\nReturns `:ok` on success or an error-handler return when initialization fails.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:init_instance/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance!/4","doc":"Same as `init_instance/4`, but raises on errors.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:init_instance!/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance_async/4","doc":"Asynchronously initializes a new instance.\n\nErrors are reported via specification error handling instead of direct return.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:init_instance_async/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.mock_instance!/4","doc":"Inserts or updates a mock instance at a given state for testing purposes.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:mock_instance!/4"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.start_link/1","doc":"Starts the instance manager process tree.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:start_link/1"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.transition/3","doc":"Records an observed transition for an existing instance.\n\nReturns `:ok` on success or an error-handler return when validation/storage fails.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:transition/3"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.transition!/3","doc":"Same as `transition/3`, but raises on errors.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:transition!/3"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.transition_async/3","doc":"Asynchronously records a transition for an existing instance.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#c:transition_async/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.__using__/1","doc":"Injects the `Spex.InstanceManager` behaviour and shared convenience functions.\n\nGenerated convenience functions:\n\n- `child_spec/1`\n- `init_instance!/4`\n- `transition!/3`","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#__using__/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.default_instance_manager/0","doc":"Returns the compile-time configured default instance manager module.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#default_instance_manager/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.default_instance_manager_opts/0","doc":"Returns compile-time options for the default instance manager.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.html#default_instance_manager_opts/0"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager","doc":"Instance manager that shards instances across multiple\n`Spex.InstanceManager.Server` processes.\n\nThis manager hashes each instance identifier and routes operations to one of\nseveral server shards. It is useful when you want to reduce contention versus\na single-manager setup while preserving the same high-level API.\n\nThis module is designed to be added directly to your supervision tree:\n\n    children = [\n      {Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager,\n       distribution_factor: 8,\n       impl_models_dir: \"./spex_impl_models\",\n       dets_dir: \"./spex_dets\"}\n    ]\n\nYou may pass options at startup or configure them in application config.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager","doc":"This manager accepts one distribution-specific option plus server options\nforwarded to each shard (`Spex.InstanceManager.Server.server_opt()`).\n\n- `:distribution_factor` (`pos_integer()`)\n  Number of server shards.\n  Default: `4`.\n  Must be a positive integer; otherwise `start_link/1` raises\n  `ArgumentError`.\n\nForwarded server options:\n\n- `:impl_models_dir` (`String.t()`)\n  Directory from which `.spex` impl models are loaded.\n  Each shard loads from the same directory at startup.\n  Default: `\"./spex_impl_models\"`.\n\n- `:dets_dir` (`String.t()`)\n  Base directory for shard DETS files.\n  Default: `\"./spex_dets\"`.\n\n- `:check_transition_timeouts_on_start?` (`boolean()`)\n  Enables startup timeout checks per shard.\n  Default: `true`.\n\n- `:prune_interval` (`timeout()`)\n  Periodic pruning interval per shard.\n  Default: `to_timeout(%Duration{hour: 6})`.\n\nPruning semantics per shard:\n\n- one prune pass is always executed immediately on shard startup,\n- when `:prune_interval != :infinity`, additional periodic prune passes are\n  scheduled,\n- when `:prune_interval == :infinity`, no periodic passes are scheduled after\n  the initial startup pass.\n\nInternal shard detail:\n\n- `:dets_table` is set per shard by this module\n  (`Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.Server_ `), so callers\n  should not provide it.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"module","title":"Option Resolution Order - Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager","doc":"For forwarded server options, each shard resolves values in this order:\n\n1. option passed to this manager at startup,\n2. application environment key under `:spex`,\n3. server default.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#module-option-resolution-order"},{"type":"module","title":"Routing Semantics - Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager","doc":"Instance routing is deterministic:\n\n- hash = `:erlang.phash2(instance_identifier)`\n- shard index = `rem(hash, distribution_factor) + 1`\n\nAll operations for a given instance identifier are routed to the same shard.\n\nMethods that aggregate globally (`all_instances/0`, `all_instances/1`,\n`delete_instances/1`, `all_impl_models/0`) query all shards and combine the\nresults.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#module-routing-semantics"},{"type":"module","title":"Application Config Example - Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager","doc":"config :spex,\n      impl_models_dir: \"./priv/spex_impl_models\",\n      dets_dir: \"./priv/spex_dets\",\n      check_transition_timeouts_on_start?: true,\n      prune_interval: :timer.hours(6)","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#module-application-config-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.all_impl_models/0","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.all_impl_models/0`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#all_impl_models/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.all_instances/0","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.all_instances/0`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#all_instances/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.all_instances/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.all_instances/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#all_instances/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.child_spec/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.child_spec/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.delete_instance/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.delete_instance/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#delete_instance/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.delete_instances/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.delete_instances/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#delete_instances/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.export_impl_models/0","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.export_impl_models/0`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#export_impl_models/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.get_instance/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.get_instance/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#get_instance/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.init_instance/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#init_instance/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.init_instance!/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance!/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#init_instance!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.init_instance_async/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance_async/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#init_instance_async/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.mock_instance!/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.mock_instance!/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#mock_instance!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.start_link/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.start_link/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.transition/3","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.transition/3`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#transition/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.transition!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.transition!/3`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#transition!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.transition_async/3","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.transition_async/3`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.html#transition_async/3"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState","doc":"Agent storing the configured distribution factor.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.distribution_factor/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.html#t:distribution_factor/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.get/0","doc":"Returns the currently configured distribution factor.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.html#get/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.start_link/1","doc":"Starts the distribution-factor agent.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager.DistributionFactorState.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance","doc":"Runtime representation of a specification instance and its observed history.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.instance_identifier/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#t:instance_identifier/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.meta/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#t:meta/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.transition_record/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#t:transition_record/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.beyond_transition_timeout?/2","doc":"Returns whether the instance exceeded its specification transition timeout.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#beyond_transition_timeout?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.initialise/3","doc":"Initialises a new instance with an empty transition history.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#initialise/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.observe_transition/3","doc":"Records an observed transition and updates the current state.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#observe_transition/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.prunable?/1","doc":"Returns whether the instance is currently eligible for pruning.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Instance.html#prunable?/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore","doc":"Abstraction layer for instance storage using DETS.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.instance_hash/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#t:instance_hash/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.all/1","doc":"Gets all instances.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#all/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.all/2","doc":"Gets all instances for a specific specification.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.close/1","doc":"Closes the DETS table.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#close/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.delete/2","doc":"Deletes an instance by hash.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.delete_matching/2","doc":"Deletes instances matching the given filter function.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#delete_matching/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.exists?/2","doc":"Checks if an instance exists for the given hash.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#exists?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.get/2","doc":"Gets an instance by hash.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#get/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.init/2","doc":"Initializes the DETS table for storing instances.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#init/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.put/2","doc":"Stores an instance with the given hash.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#put/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.traverse/2","doc":"Traverses all instances with the given function.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#traverse/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.truncate/1","doc":"Deletes all instances from the DETS table.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore.html#truncate/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server","doc":"Core GenServer that manages instances and implementation-model observation.\n\nThis process is the stateful runtime engine behind both simple and\ndistributed instance managers.\n\nResponsibilities include:\n\n- loading implementation models on startup,\n- storing and retrieving instances via `Spex.InstanceManager.InstanceStore`,\n- validating observed transitions against implementation models,\n- scheduling transition timeout checks,\n- pruning stale instances.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.impl_models_map/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.html#t:impl_models_map/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.server_opt/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.html#t:server_opt/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.server_state/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.html#t:server_state/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.Server.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager","doc":"Single-node instance manager backed by one `Spex.InstanceManager.Server` process.\n\nUse this manager when you want all instance operations handled by a single\nGenServer and a single DETS table.\n\nThis module is designed to be added directly to your supervision tree, e.g.\nvia `child_spec/1`:\n\n    children = [\n      {Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager,\n       impl_models_dir: \"./spex_impl_models\",\n       dets_dir: \"./spex_dets\"}\n    ]\n\nYou may provide runtime options when starting this manager, or provide the\nsame values via application environment (`config/*.exs`).","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Configuration - Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager","doc":"`SimpleInstanceManager` forwards server options to\n`Spex.InstanceManager.Server` (see `server_opt()`), with one internal detail:\n\n- `:dets_table` is always set to `Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager`\n  by this module and should not be provided by callers.\n\nSupported options:\n\n- `:impl_models_dir` (`String.t()`)\n  Path to `.spex` implementation model files loaded on startup.\n  Default: `\"./spex_impl_models\"`.\n\n- `:dets_dir` (`String.t()`)\n  Directory where the DETS file for this manager is stored.\n  Default: `\"./spex_dets\"`.\n\n- `:check_transition_timeouts_on_start?` (`boolean()`)\n  When `true`, existing instances in DETS are checked during startup and\n  transition timeout errors are emitted if needed.\n  Default: `true`.\n\n- `:prune_interval` (`timeout()`)\n  Interval for periodic pruning checks. Use `:infinity` to disable periodic\n  checks after startup.\n  Default: `to_timeout(%Duration{hour: 6})`.\n\nPruning semantics:\n\n- one prune pass is always executed immediately on startup,\n- when `:prune_interval != :infinity`, additional periodic prune passes are\n  scheduled,\n- when `:prune_interval == :infinity`, no periodic passes are scheduled after\n  the initial startup pass.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#module-configuration"},{"type":"module","title":"Option Resolution Order - Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager","doc":"For each server option, effective value is resolved in this order:\n\n1. option passed to `start_link/1` / supervisor child spec,\n2. application environment key under `:spex`,\n3. server default.\n\nMissing required values raise with a descriptive `ArgumentError`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#module-option-resolution-order"},{"type":"module","title":"Application Config Example - Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager","doc":"config :spex,\n      impl_models_dir: \"./priv/spex_impl_models\",\n      dets_dir: \"./priv/spex_dets\",\n      check_transition_timeouts_on_start?: true,\n      prune_interval: :timer.hours(6)","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#module-application-config-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.all_impl_models/0","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.all_impl_models/0`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#all_impl_models/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.all_instances/0","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.all_instances/0`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#all_instances/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.all_instances/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.all_instances/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#all_instances/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.child_spec/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.child_spec/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.delete_instance/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.delete_instance/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#delete_instance/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.delete_instances/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.delete_instances/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#delete_instances/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.export_impl_models/0","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.export_impl_models/0`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#export_impl_models/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.get_instance/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.get_instance/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#get_instance/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.init_instance/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#init_instance/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.init_instance!/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance!/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#init_instance!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.init_instance_async/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.init_instance_async/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#init_instance_async/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.mock_instance!/4","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.mock_instance!/4`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#mock_instance!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.start_link/1","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.start_link/1`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.transition/3","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.transition/3`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#transition/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.transition!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.transition!/3`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#transition!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.transition_async/3","doc":"Callback implementation for `c:Spex.InstanceManager.transition_async/3`.","ref":"Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager.html#transition_async/3"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Spex.Specification","doc":"Behaviour and DSL for defining specifications through labelled transition systems (LTSs).\n\nA specification module describes the expected states, actions, and transitions\nof a system. Spex uses this information to:\n\n- validate observed runtime behaviour,\n- construct and maintain implementation models,\n- check branching bisimilarity between model and specification,\n- enforce transition timeout and pruning policies.\n\nThis module provides:\n\n- behaviour callbacks that every specification must implement,\n- a `use` macro that generates those callbacks from a concise DSL,\n- `def_transition/3` for declaring transitions,\n- default error handling that can be overridden per specification.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Configuration Options - Spex.Specification","doc":"Pass options to `use Spex.Specification, ...`.\n\n### `:transition_timeout`\n\nMaximum time between two observed transitions for an instance.\n\n- Default: `:infinity`\n- Accepted values: `:infinity`, integer milliseconds, or `%Duration{}`\n  (converted via `to_timeout/1`)\n- Used by instance manager timeout checks.\n\nIf an instance exceeds this timeout, Spex emits\n`%Spex.Errors.TransitionError{reason: :transition_timeout}` and routes it\nthrough the specification `error_handler/2`.\n\n### `:prune_timeout`\n\nMinimum idle time before an instance can be considered for pruning.\n\n- Default: `:infinity`\n- Accepted values: `:infinity`, integer milliseconds, or `%Duration{}`\n  (converted via `to_timeout/1`)\n\nPruning eligibility also depends on `:prunable_states`.\n\n### `:prunable_states`\n\nControls which states are allowed to be pruned after `:prune_timeout`.\n\n- Default: `[]` (no states are prunable)\n- Accepted values:\n  - `:all`: any current state may be pruned\n  - `:terminal`: only terminal states may be pruned\n  - explicit state list, e.g. `[:done, :failed]`\n\nTerminal states are derived from transitions as states with no outgoing edge.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#module-configuration-options"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Transition DSL - Spex.Specification","doc":"Define transitions with `def_transition(from_state, action, to_state)`.\n\nEach call contributes to compile-time metadata used to generate:\n\n- `states/0`\n- `actions/0`\n- `transitions/0`\n- `initial_state/0`\n- `terminal_states/0`\n\nDuplicate states/actions/transitions are deduplicated.\n\nThe initial state is the source state of the first declared transition.\nIf no transitions are declared, `initial_state/0` returns `nil`.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#module-transition-dsl"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Generated Callbacks - Spex.Specification","doc":"When you `use Spex.Specification`, the following callbacks are generated\nautomatically:\n\n- `transition_timeout/0`\n- `prune_timeout/0`\n- `prunable_states/0`\n- `states/0`\n- `actions/0`\n- `transitions/0`\n- `initial_state/0`\n- `terminal_states/0`\n- `error_handler/2` (delegates to `default_error_handler/2` by default)\n\n`error_handler/2` is overridable.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#module-generated-callbacks"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Error Handling Contract - Spex.Specification","doc":"`error_handler/2` receives `(error, caller_pid)` and must return:\n\n- `:ok` to swallow/accept the error condition, or\n- `{:error, reason}` to propagate failure.\n\nDefault behaviour in `default_error_handler/2`:\n\n- logs the error and caller stacktrace,\n- returns `:ok` for:\n  - `%Spex.Errors.TransitionError{reason: :deviation_still_bisimilar}`\n  - `%Spex.Errors.ImplModelError{reason: :impl_model_not_found}`\n- returns `{:error, error}` for all other errors.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#module-error-handling-contract"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"Full Example - Spex.Specification","doc":"defmodule MySpec do\n      use Spex.Specification,\n        transition_timeout: 30_000,\n        prune_timeout: %Duration{hour: 1},\n        prunable_states: :terminal\n\n      def_transition :idle, :start, :running\n      def_transition :running, :complete, :done\n      def_transition :running, :fail, :failed\n\n      @impl Spex.Specification\n      def error_handler(error, caller) do\n        send(caller, {:spec_error, error})\n        {:error, error}\n      end\n    end","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#module-full-example"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Specification.error_handler_return/0","doc":"The return type for `error_handler/2` callbacks.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#t:error_handler_return/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Specification.t/0","doc":"A module implementing this behaviour","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"Spex.Specification.error_handler/2","doc":"Callback for handling errors emitted by Spex during instance management.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#c:error_handler/2"},{"type":"macro","title":"Spex.Specification.def_transition/3","doc":"Defines a transition from one state to another via an action.\n\nThe first state of the first transition becomes the initial state.\nStates and actions are automatically collected and deduplicated.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#def_transition/3"},{"type":"macro","title":"Example - Spex.Specification.def_transition/3","doc":"def_transition :idle, :start, :working\n    def_transition :working, :complete, :idle","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#def_transition/3-example"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.Specification.default_error_handler/2","doc":"Default error handling strategy used by specification modules.","ref":"Spex.Specification.html#default_error_handler/2"},{"type":"module","title":"Spex.Testing","doc":"Test helpers for preparing and manipulating Spex runtime state.","ref":"Spex.Testing.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Testing.opt/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Testing.html#t:opt/0"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.Testing.mock_instance!/4","doc":"Inserts or updates a mock instance at a specific state for test setup.","ref":"Spex.Testing.html#mock_instance!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"Spex.Testing.prepare_for_test_suite/1","doc":"Prepares after-suite hooks that export collected implementation models.","ref":"Spex.Testing.html#prepare_for_test_suite/1"},{"type":"exception","title":"Spex.Errors.DetsError","doc":"DETS backend operation errors.","ref":"Spex.Errors.DetsError.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.DetsError.reason/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.DetsError.html#t:reason/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.DetsError.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.DetsError.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"exception","title":"Spex.Errors.ImplModelError","doc":"ImplModel loading and lookup errors.","ref":"Spex.Errors.ImplModelError.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.ImplModelError.reason/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.ImplModelError.html#t:reason/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.ImplModelError.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.ImplModelError.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"exception","title":"Spex.Errors.InstanceError","doc":"Instance lifecycle errors such as duplicate or missing identifiers.","ref":"Spex.Errors.InstanceError.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.InstanceError.reason/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.InstanceError.html#t:reason/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.InstanceError.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.InstanceError.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"exception","title":"Spex.Errors.TransitionError","doc":"Transition-level error used for deviations and timeout conditions.","ref":"Spex.Errors.TransitionError.html"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.TransitionError.reason/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.TransitionError.html#t:reason/0"},{"type":"type","title":"Spex.Errors.TransitionError.t/0","doc":"","ref":"Spex.Errors.TransitionError.html#t:t/0"},{"type":"extras","title":"Spex","doc":"# Spex\n\nSpex is an Elixir library for checking whether a system behaves like its specification.\n\nIt lets you describe expected behaviour as a labelled transition system, observe\nreal transitions at runtime or during tests, derive an implementation model from\nthose observations, and compare the result against the specification in terms of\nbehavioural equivalence. In this sense, Spex brings a portion of formal verification\ntheory to Elixir practice and can help you detect whether your implementation \ndeviates from a given specification of a workflow or protocol.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"What Spex Does - Spex","doc":"Spex combines a few pieces into one workflow:\n\n1. A DSL for defining specifications as labelled transition systems.\n2. Runtime APIs for tracking instance lifecycles and observed transitions.\n3. Persistent implementation model storage in `.spex` files.\n4. Offline verification with `mix spex`.\n\nThis makes it possible to use Spex in two complementary ways:\n\n- online, while your application is running,\n- offline, by deriving models from tests and checking them afterwards.","ref":"readme.html#what-spex-does"},{"type":"extras","title":"Typical Workflow - Spex","doc":"","ref":"readme.html#typical-workflow"},{"type":"extras","title":"1. Define a specification - Spex","doc":"```elixir\ndefmodule MyApp.OrderSpec do\n  use Spex.Specification,\n    transition_timeout: 30_000,\n    prune_timeout: %Duration{hour: 1},\n    prunable_states: :terminal\n\n  def_transition :new, :pay, :paid\n  def_transition :paid, :ship, :shipped\n  def_transition :paid, :cancel, :cancelled\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#1-define-a-specification"},{"type":"extras","title":"2. Start Spex - Spex","doc":"You can either let Spex run as its own OTP application, or add it explicitly to\nyour supervision tree.\n\nIf you want explicit control, you can supervise:\n\n- `Spex`\n- `Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager`\n- `Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager`\n\nExample:\n\n```elixir\nchildren = [\n  {Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager,\n   impl_models_dir: \"./spex_impl_models\",\n   dets_dir: \"./spex_dets\"}\n]\n```\n\nIf you choose to supervise Spex this way, you should configure the dependency \nwith `runtime: false`.","ref":"readme.html#2-start-spex"},{"type":"extras","title":"3. Observe real behaviour - Spex","doc":"```elixir\nSpex.init_instance!(MyApp.OrderSpec, :order_123)\nSpex.transition!(:order_123, :pay, :paid)\nSpex.transition!(:order_123, :ship, :shipped)\n```\n\nSpex records the observed transitions, updates the implementation model, and can\nreport deviations or timeouts through the specification error handler.","ref":"readme.html#3-observe-real-behaviour"},{"type":"extras","title":"4. Check derived models offline - Spex","doc":"Spex can export implementation models as `.spex` files and verify them with the\nMix task:\n\n```sh\nmix spex\n```\n\nor:\n\n```sh\nmix spex path/to/impl_models\n```\n\nThis is especially useful in CI or after a test suite has produced derived\nmodels.","ref":"readme.html#4-check-derived-models-offline"},{"type":"extras","title":"Deriving ImplModels From Tests - Spex","doc":"One of the main use cases for Spex is deriving implementation models from test\nexecution and then validating them afterwards.\n\nUse `Spex.Testing.prepare_for_test_suite/1` in your test setup:\n\n```elixir\n# test/test_helper.exs\nSpex.Testing.prepare_for_test_suite(\n  impl_models_dir: \"./test_meta/impl_models/live\"\n)\n```\n\nThen run your tests as normal. After the suite finishes, Spex exports the\nderived models. From there, `mix spex` becomes the verification step that tells\nyou whether the observed behaviour is still bisimilar to the specification.","ref":"readme.html#deriving-implmodels-from-tests"},{"type":"extras","title":"Why Branching Bisimilarity? - Spex","doc":"Spex does not just compare raw transition lists.\n\nIt uses branching bisimilarity, which is useful when implementations contain\ninternal transitions that should not count as observable deviations. This lets\nyou distinguish between:\n\n- harmless internal implementation detail,\n- genuine behavioural change.\n\nThat is the key idea behind the library: treat specifications as executable,\ncheckable behavioural contracts instead of static documentation.","ref":"readme.html#why-branching-bisimilarity"},{"type":"extras","title":"Theoretical Background - Spex","doc":"Spex is motivated by ideas from concurrency theory and behavioural semantics.\n\nAt a high level, the library treats a system as a labelled transition system\n(LTS): a set of states connected by observable actions and, optionally,\ninternal steps. From there, the natural question is not just whether two\nsystems have the same implementation, but whether they exhibit the same\nobservable behaviour.\n\nThat is where behavioural equivalence comes in. In Spex, the main notion is\nbisimilarity, and more specifically branching bisimilarity. This matters because\nreal systems often contain internal transitions that should not count as user-\nvisible deviations. Two implementations may differ operationally while still\nbeing behaviourally equivalent.\n\nYou can also think of Spex as living near refinement checking:\n\n- the specification defines allowed behaviour,\n- the derived implementation model captures observed behaviour,\n- the checker asks whether the implementation still refines the intent of the\n  specification under the chosen equivalence notion.\n\nSpex does not aim to be a full model checker or a theorem prover. The goal is\nmore pragmatic: bring a useful slice of formal behavioural reasoning into an\nordinary Elixir workflow.\n\nIf those topics are new to you, the most relevant search terms are:\n\n- concurrency theory\n- labelled transition systems\n- behavioural equivalence\n- bisimilarity\n- branching bisimilarity\n- refinement checking","ref":"readme.html#theoretical-background"},{"type":"extras","title":"Documentation - Spex","doc":"The main documentation lives in the moduledocs and is intended to be published\nwith ExDoc.\n\nThe most important entry points are:\n\n- `Spex` for high-level usage and integration\n- `Spex.Specification` for defining specifications\n- `Spex.InstanceManager` for manager behaviour and callbacks\n- `Spex.InstanceManager.SimpleInstanceManager` for the single-node runtime\n- `Spex.InstanceManager.DistributedInstanceManager` for the sharded runtime\n- `Spex.Testing` for test integration\n- `Mix.Tasks.Spex` for offline verification\n\nNote that Spex is in its early stages. This documentation will be expanded and possibly rewritten in the near future, as it is in large parts AI-generated as of now, which I'm not a huge fan of, to be honest, but judged to be good enough for a first release.","ref":"readme.html#documentation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - Spex","doc":"Add `spex` to your dependencies:\n\n```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:lts_spex, \"~> 0.1.0\"}\n  ]\nend\n```\n\nNote that the package name is `:lts_spex` rather than just `:spex`, since that was [already taken](https://hex.pm/packages/spex) (which I realised only after becoming attached to the name). Since the latter package is unmaintained and little used, I decided to keep the namespace simply as `Spex`.\n\nIf you plan to supervise Spex yourself, you can also choose a `runtime: false`\nintegration style and add `Spex` or one of the instance managers to your own\nsupervision tree explicitly.","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Credits - Spex","doc":"Spex uses a NIF written in Rust to perform the bisimilarity check. Concretely, the crate [`merc_reduction`](https://docs.rs/merc_reduction/1.0.0/merc_reduction/) is used. I want to thank [Maurice Laveaux](https://github.com/mlaveaux) for implementing this efficient tool and making it available!","ref":"readme.html#credits"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.2"}}